  "issueDetected": true,
  "declaredLane": "documentation lifecycle, repo-imported skill management, skill route registry coverage, recurrence closeout coverage, and rules-only validation coverage",
  "observedMutationClass": "global Codex skill import into repo-local .codex/skills, repo-imported skill managed-document discovery, skill trigger matrix coverage, repo-imported rule skill route registry lint, optional external skill link lint demotion, rule-harness rules-only scope expansion, active plan artifact owner shape drift guard preservation, active plan concrete artifact owner collision guard preservation, progress evidence overload guard preservation, and recurrence closeout update",
  "acceptanceEvidenceClass": "docs-lint fixture tests, rules:sync-closeout, and full rules lint; no gameplay or Unity runtime acceptance evidence",
  "escalationRequired": false,
  "rootCause": "The repo previously treated many reusable Codex skills as outside-home installed state, so JG routing could describe rule skills without guaranteeing that the bodies, bundled references, scripts, or relative links were git-trackable in this repo. Managed document discovery and rules-only recurrence targeting were still biased toward repo-local JG skill entries, which made imported skill drift easy to miss while other existing policy guards such as active plan artifact owner shape drift, active plan concrete artifact owner collisions, and progress evidence overload remained the only broadly enforced shape checks.",
  "prevention": "Keep global Codex skills imported under .codex/skills/ when they influence JG repo behavior, exclude only .codex/skills/.system from repo-managed skill lifecycle, discover every repo-imported skill markdown file in docs-lint without requiring owner metadata for generic bundled skill docs, and make rules-only recurrence targets include .codex/skills/* paths. Keep skill_routing_registry and skill_trigger_matrix phrased around repo-imported skills, preserve regression tests for imported skill link checks, and preserve the existing hard-fail checks for active plan artifact owner shape drift, active plan concrete artifact owner collisions, and progress evidence overload.",
  "verification": "node --test tools/docs-lint/tests/docs-lint.test.mjs; npm run --silent docs:health -- --json; npm run --silent docs:lint; npm run --silent rules:sync-closeout; npm run --silent rules:lint",
